collection.description:
Erin E brings an ear for unique sounds to her energetic and genre-bending dj sets.  Integrating global gems with sometimes heavy, sometimes heavenly percussive and melodic force, she strips back dance music to something we all can relate to.  Constantly searching for the essence of the sound - be it deep & dub techno, electronic folklore, house or beyond- she cultivates a bassy dancefloor (and headphone) experience that transcends stereotype. 

She is currently working on an ongoing series of place-based 'immersive' mixes, created and performed in wild spaces alone or with a very small crew of intimate listeners.  

Playing & sampling her original live native american flute, didjeridoo, shakers and myriad of trinkets, she sneaks authentic sound into unexpected places.


Based in Santa Fe, NM, Erin E loves, above all, creating the space for a transformative, positive experience through music and creative community.

BIO . PORTUGUÊS (PT-BR) 
Nascido em Fortaleza-CE em 1985, Yuri Steindorfer iniciou sua vida musical em 2001 como guitarrista. Com uma vasta influência musical, já tocou em bandas de hardcore (Crash), blues (Blusenroll) e samba rock psicodélico(Transcenda!). Iniciou sua carreira de Dj depois que se apaixonou pela música eletrônica, profissionalizando-se através de cursos pesquisas e muito comprometimento. Unindo paixão com experiência e sensibilidade musical, já realizou belas apresentações, inclusive internacionais quando morou uma temporada na Irlanda (em 2012).
Em junho de 2015 passou a fazer parte do casting de Dj's e colaboradores do Cenaceara.dj e Eubiose Ecofestival.
Com uma musicalidade autêntica e mixagens dinâmicas, seu set é carregado de muito groove e psicodelia séria! 


► BIO . ENGLISH (EN) 
Born in 1985, in Fortaleza-CE, Yuri Steindorfer started his music life in 2001 like guitarrist. With a great musical influence he played with a hardcore band(Crash), blues band (Blues'n roll) and psychedelic samba-rock band (Transcenda!)
Started his Dj carrer since he fell in love by the eletronic music. Mixing passion with musical experience and musical sensibility he did some great Plays around the world when he lived in Dublin(IE). 
His set is full of groove and psychedelic sounds!

Sharps hails from Vancouver BC, and pushes at the edges of dance music, fusing west coast bass, carribean riddim and UK underground. Diversity and dancefloor bounce are the mission.

Sharps began crafting beats amidst the early rave culture and IDM experimentation of the 90s. Since those days, his music has grown, and brought him to international stages from London UK, to the bay area, and back home to Vancouver BC. A few early breakthrough tunes from '07-'09 put his name on the bass music map, with Night Work, Girl Sweat, and his remix of Ginuwine's Pony. Voyages through the Americas inspired the fusion of reggaeton and dancehall into west coast bass music, and he began producing his signature dembow bass tunes. Sharps blurs the edges of genre to create hybrid dancefloor tunes.

griff is one of Australia’s leading purveyors of highly varied and unique bass music.  Since 2009, griff has created many LPs, EPs and remixes, released on renowned labels such as Omelette, Addictech, Enig'Matik Records, Slurp Music and Buxton Records.  

As an assistant engineer at Sing Sing Studios in Melbourne, Australia he worked on albums by The Cat Empire, The Jon Butler Trio, Blue King Brown, The Dirty Three and many more. 

Playing his original compositions and DJing all manner of styles and genres he has toured the world moving crowds at festivals such as Shambhala Music Festival in Canada, Boom in Portugal, Symbiosis and Burning Man in the US and Rainbow Serpent Festival in his home country of Australia. 

He enjoys laughing and is uncomfortable talking in the 3rd person.

Timmy Hogan, DJ (the radio kind)91.7FM Mana'o Radio Maui or stream: http://manaoradio.com  (doing fill-in slots only 2017)). Also promoting family art: http://VanVlietArt.com 

Music is my lifelong passion.  I try to be an instigator and facilitator. I like to drop pianos in places that need them. I am most interested in bridging the acoustic and digital worlds, promoting the language of music (which I fear is being lost), especially the language of jazz (America's classical music).  I have been playing music since a child, on many instruments, piano (my current focus), guitar, bass, drums, kalimba, mbira, harmonica, ukelele, banjo, mandolin, percussion, and more.  

I'm beginning to play out more on Maui and hope to make a positive contribution to its music scene, like at Charley's open mic on Monday evenings in Pa'ia. 

I promote music education and the language of jazz harmonics as a sophisticated learning tool that spans genres. I am also working on a book for teaching piano and jazz theory for ear players. I have a degree in ethnomusicology from UC Boulder.  I've been involved with Burning Man since 2004, bringing my own installation in 2011, The Piano Liberation Project.  I have done many guerrilla/renegade performances at many events, including Burning Man, Lightning In A Bottle (even just whipping out the harmonica and adding accents to the dub set- hey, it worked!), Xingolati, Priceless, Decompression, and others.
